### Reproduction

Steps to reproduce:
1. Add `@angular/cdk` to the project
2. Import `OverlayModule`
3. Inject Overlay to some component through DI
4. Create a portal to render the template (you should define it in the HTML + query it thourgh ViewChild)
5. Create an overlay
6. Attach portal to the overlay

I created two examples on stackblits with ivy and without ivy. Looks like stackblitz can not work in ivy mode. You can clone the example and execute `npm i` && `ng serve --open`. You will be able to reproduce the problem (links are below).

Looks like the problem is strongly connected with `NgIfDirective` since if you remove it everything works fine.

#### Examples (stackblitz, github repos)

##### With Ivy:
Stackblitz example does not work in Ivy mode despite of enableIvy flags in the angularCompilerOptions section of the `tsconfig` file. Looks like Ivy is not working in stackblitz. You can check tsconfig, it is enabled. Tell me please if it can be easily fixed.

